fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.neoemf.query

Class NeoEMFQueryResult

  • Object
    • QueryResult
      • NeoEMFQueryResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Object>

    public class NeoEMFQueryResult
extends QueryResult
    A NeoEMF-based implementation of QueryResult that provides utility methods to reify datastore query result and return EObjects that can be used within a NeoEMF-based application.

    This class is used by the dedicated NeoEMF AbstractQueryProcessors to ease the integration of Mogwai in existing EMF-based applications. Note that NeoEMF AbstractQueryProcessors only support a graph backend that stores model elements according to the NeoEMFMapping.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL

    • Constructor Detail

      • NeoEMFQueryResult

        public NeoEMFQueryResult(Object engineResult,
                         BlueprintsPersistenceBackend graph,
                         String gremlinScript)
        Constructs a new NeoEMFQueryResult from the given engineResult, graph, and literal gremlinScript.

        Note: if engineResult is an instance of Iterable this constructor iterates it to wrap the results. In case of Gremlin-based queries this can be costly because GremlinPipeline content is computed when iterated.

        Parameters:
        engineResult - the result of the query computation
        graph - the BlueprintsPersistenceBackend used to reify results as EObjects
        gremlinScript - the textual representation of the computed query

      • NeoEMFQueryResult

        public NeoEMFQueryResult(Object engineResult,
                         BlueprintsPersistenceBackend graph,
                         GremlinScript gremlinScript)
        Constructs a new NeoEMFQueryResult from the given engineResult, graph, and gremlinScript.

        Note: if engineResult is an instance of Iterable this constructor iterates it to wrap the results. In case of Gremlin-based queries this can be costly because GremlinPipeline content is computed when iterated.

        Parameters:
        engineResult - the result of the query computation
        graph - the BlueprintsPersistenceBackend used to reify results as EObjects
        gremlinScript - the GremlinScript element representing the root of the computed query

      • reifyResults

        public List<EObject> reifyResults(PersistentResource resource)
                           throws MogwaiCoreException
        Reifies the query result as EObjects and attach them to the provided resource.

        This method is specific to NeoEMFQueryResult, that can use NeoEMF BlueprintsPersistenceBackend to create EObjects from graph vertices. Reified elements can be used as standard EObjects stored in NeoEMF.

        Parameters:
        resource - the Resource to attach the reified EObjects to
        Returns:
        a List containing the reified EObjects
        Throws:
        MogwaiCoreException - if the query result cannot be reified by the backend

      • iterator

        public Iterator<Object> iterator()
        Returns a new Iterator on the query result.

        Note: the returned Iterator doesn't reify the result, even if it is possible. To access reified result see reifyResults(PersistentResource).
